Amina Elias","date":"July 29, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO people, there are no more glad tidings of prophecy except righteous dreams seen by a Muslim, or he is made to see. Verily, I have been prohibited from reciting the Quran while bowing or prostrating\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33032,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/what-to-say-ruku-sujud\/","url_meta":{"origin":5664,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: What to say when bowing, prostrating in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hudhayfah ibn al-Yaman reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said three times while bowing in prayer, \u201cGlory to my Lord, the Almighty,\u201d and he said three times while prostrating in prayer, \u201cGlory to my Lord, the Most High.\u201d Source: Sunan Ibn Ma\u0304jah 888 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33026,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/prophets-dua-ruku-sujud\/","url_meta":{"origin":5664,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salat: The Prophet&#8217;s supplication in bowing, prostration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would say in his bowing and prostration, \u201cGlory be to you, Allah our Lord, and your praises. Forgive me.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4042, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 484 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33168,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/11\/imam-rabbana-lakal-hamd\/","url_meta":{"origin":5664,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Salat: What to say when Imam rises in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the Imam says, \u2018Allah heard those who praise him,\u2019 then say, \u2018Our Lord, for you is praise.\u2019 If one\u2019s statement coincides with the statement of the angels, his previous sins will be forgiven.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33024,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/minimum-tasbih-ruku-sajda\/","url_meta":{"origin":5664,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Glorifying Allah minimum three times in bowing, prostrating","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen one of you bows in prayer, let him say three times in his bowing: Glory be to my Lord, the Greatest. He will have completed his bowing and that is the least of it. Let him say\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33925,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/13\/dua-rising-from-ruku\/","url_meta":{"origin":5664,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Salat: The Prophet\u2019s supplication rising from bowing","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 13, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Awfa reported: When the Messegner of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, raised his back from bowing, he would say, \u201cAllah has heard one who praised Him. O Allah, our Lord, to You belong praise as fills the heavens, fills the earth, and fills anything You will\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/5664","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=5664"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/5664\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=5664"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=5664"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=5664"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}